functions.name: runccx

parsed_metadata.description: Runs Calculix with specified parameters, allowing for output visualization and controlled termination. Supports both Windows and Linux environments.

inputs.name: output_folder
inputs.description: Path to the output folder where results and logs will be stored. (Required)

inputs.name: name_inp
inputs.description: Name of the input file for Calculix. (Required)

inputs.name: OMP_NUM_THREADS
inputs.description: Number of threads to use for parallel execution. Default is 8. (Optional)

inputs.name: outtxt
inputs.description: Name of the output log file. Default is 'out.txt'. (Optional)

inputs.name: mpi
inputs.description: Flag to enable MPI execution. Default is False. (Optional)

inputs.name: mpi_np
inputs.description: Number of MPI processes to use if MPI is enabled. Default is 4. (Optional)

outputs.description: Returns a tuple containing the error code (0 for success, 1 for failure) and the command used to run Calculix.

functions.name: frd2json

parsed_metadata.name: frd2json
parsed_metadata.description: Converts finite element data from an inp (djccx.inp.inp) and a results file (FRD) into a JSON-compatible dictionary structure.

inputs.name: inpf
inputs.description: The input file object, typically containing nodes, elements, and boundary conditions.

inputs.name: elements
inputs.description: A list of surface elements to be included in the conversion. If not provided, all elements from 'inpf' will be used.

inputs.name: frd
inputs.description: The results file object containing node displacements and additional results. If not provided, the default results stored in 'inpf.frd' are used.

outputs.description: A dictionary containing the processed data for further use or visualization.

keys.name: i
keys.description: Node indices (i) defining faces of surface elements.

keys.name: j
keys.description: Node indices (j) defining faces of surface elements.

keys.name: k
keys.description: Node indices (k) defining faces of surface elements.

keys.name: i_list
keys.description: List of node indices (i) for individual surfaces.

keys.name: j_list
keys.description: List of node indices (j) for individual surfaces.

keys.name: k_list
keys.description: List of node indices (k) for individual surfaces.

functions.name: CreateSkeletonFromTrajs
CreateSkeletonFromTrajs
CreateNsetFromElementIndex
functions.docstring:
Creates a node set (nset) from the given element indices.

Parameters:
- self: The object containing the list of elements and nodes from the .inp file.
- index_el (list[int]): A list of element indices from which the node set will be created.
- name (str, optional): The name of the nset. If not provided, the name will default to the last element's ELSET.

Returns:
- NsetCard: The created nset (node set) containing unique nodes from the elements.

functions.name: CreateNsetFromElement
functions.docstring:
Creates a node set (nset) from a list of elements.

Parameters:
- self: The object containing the list of elements and nodes from the .inp file.
- elements (list): A list of element objects from which the node set will be created.
- name (str): The name of the nset to be created.

Returns:
- NsetCard: The created nset (node set) containing unique nodes from the elements.

functions.name: read

parsed_metadata.description: This function processes a string to create an ElsetCard or ElsetofElsetCard object. The string is formatted, cleaned, and converted into an integer array or a list depending on the case.

inputs.name: content
inputs.description: Content representing input data in comma-separated text format, possibly containing newline characters.

inputs.name: name
inputs.description: Name of the card, which may include the prefix 'ELSET=' at the beginning.

outputs.description: Returns an ElsetCard object if the content can be converted into an integer array. Otherwise, returns an ElsetofElsetCard object.
